Important notes:
-----------------
1. Logical operators are &&, || and !.

2. Logical operators are useful in 2 situations :
	1) Checking ranges  2)Solving yes/no problem
		
3. sizeof is an operator. It gives number of bytes occupied by an entity.

4. Conditional operators ?: are ternary operators. General form :
	?: can have only 1 statement each
	?: can be nested
	?: always go together. : is not optional.
	
5. Always paranthesis assignment operation is used with ?:

